This paper is primarily focused on credit card fraud detection using machine learning algorithms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of different sampling methods and ensemble models, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of cost-based metrics to evaluate algorithm performance, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cyber security (cs.CY). Finally, the paper uses Monte Carlo simulations to evaluate algorithm performance, which is a technique commonly used in data science (cs.DS).
